@node "INSTALLATION" "Installation of SysOp-DL"
@{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}

 Just click on the supplied Install Icon to Install SysOp-Download via the
 Installer. This script will set everything for you including the Tooltypes.

 If you want to install it by yourself, follow these steps:

 1. Copy the SysOpDL/ Drawer to your DOORS: drawer or wherever you have
    stored your BBS-Tools.

 2. Edit the ToolTypes from the SysOp-Download Icon to your needs.

 3. Depending on your BBS-System follow this step now:

    @{u}For AMIEX-Users:@{uu}

    Copy the Icon @{b}COMMANDS/BBSCMD/DS.INFO@{ub} to your @{b}BBS:COMMANDS/BBSCMD/@{ub}
    drawer and adjust (if needed) the @{b}LOCATION@{ub} Tooltype to the path
    were SysOp-Download could be found.

    -------------------------------------------------------------------

    @{u}For FAME-Users:@{uu}

    Copy the Door-Definition from @{b}SETTINGS/DOORS/BBSCMD/DS@{ub} to your
    @{b}FAME:SETTINGS/DOORS/BBSCMD/@{ub} drawer. Now start SystemEditor, load in
    the BBSCMD "@{b}DS@{ub}" and adjust the path to SysOp-Download. Don't forget
    to save back the definition!

 4. If you have installed SysOp-Download with the Installer-Script, you
    should now read the Chapter @{"Usage of SysOp-Download" link "USAGE" 0}, all others should
    take a look to the @{"ToolTypes" link "TOOLTYPES" 0} to setup the Program correctly!
@endnode

@node "TOOLTYPES" "All Tooltypes from SysOp-DL"
 @{b}ALL TOOLTYPE-INFORMATIONS@{ub}

Now following a list of all currently supported Tooltypes:

  @{fg shine}TOOLTYPE:@{fg text} @{b}|@{ub}@{fg shine} DESCRIPTION:@{fg text} 
 @{b}-----------+---------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
 PASSWORD   @{b}|@{ub} This is the only Tooltype which is absolutly needed for
            @{b}|@{ub} SysOp-Download. If you don't specify it, it won't work ! Enter
            @{b}|@{ub} here a Password (max. 40 Chars, not case-sensitive!) which
            @{b}|@{ub} will be used as Securitycheck every time the Door starts. 
 @{b}-----------+---------------------------------------------------------------@{ub} 
 TEMP_PATH  @{b}|@{ub} When you plan to use the Pack-Option of SysOpDL, you MUST (!)
            @{b}|@{ub} enter here a valid ADOS-Path. This path is used to pack all
            @{b}|@{ub} selected files into an archive  which will be created into
            @{b}|@{ub} this path, so make sure that enough Bytes are free! If this
            @{b}|@{ub} Tooltype isn't present, it's impossible to download complete
            @{b}|@{ub} dirs,  as directories are always packed by SysOpDL ! 
 @{b}-----------+---------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
 LHA        @{b}|@{ub} Here you should enter the full path of the packers you want to 
 LZX        @{b}|@{ub} use with SysOpDL, i.e. LHA=PACKERS:LHA. If some of this Tool- 
 ZIP        @{b}|@{ub} types are not available, the according packers won't be shown
            @{b}|@{ub} in the 'Choose-Packer' List.
@endnode

